    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nMost of the newer plugins are distributed as `<something>.nvim`.\n\nIf I have the repo locally and would like to run `:chechealth <something>`, it falls saying that `<something>.nvim.health` doesn't exist.\n\nOf course, I could simply rename the directory. But in `lua/vim/health.lua`, I am seeing that `.vim` paths are handled differently. So, it would be nice to have something similar for `.nvim` ones.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nHandle `<something>.nvim` as if they are loaded as `<something>`.\n\nSomething like this,\n\n```diff\ndiff --git a/old_h.lua b/new_h.lua\nindex 5ca465a..154872a 100644\n--- a/old_h.lua\n+++ b/new_h.lua\n@@ -149,7 +149,12 @@ local function filepath_to_healthcheck(path)\n     end\n     name = assert(name:gsub('/', '.')) --- @type string\n\n-    func = 'require(\"' .. name .. '.health\").check()'\n+    if name:find('%.nvim') then\n+      func = 'require(\"' .. name:match(\"([^\\\\//%.]+)%.nvim\") .. '.health\").check()'\n+    else\n+      func = 'require(\"' .. name .. '.health\").check()'\n+    end\n+\n     filetype = 'l'\n   end\n   return { name, func, filetype }\n```",
