            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> in `lua/vim/health.lua`, I am seeing that `.vim` paths are handled differently. So, it would be nice to have something similar for `.nvim` ones.\n\n`.vim` is a filetype, like `.lua`, it is not treating directory names differently.\n\nSpecial-casing checkhealth in this way will cause confusion, not to mention potential conflicts.\n\nCan't really do much here until we have a deterministic way to identify plugins, i.e. to decide a plugins \"name\". That is discussed in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/35854",
